Chicago is known for its steakhouses. There are many that advertise and cater to the bar scene and celebrities. Erie does none of the above although there are always some interesting people there but, they go for the food and not for celebrity. I have been to all the so called great steakhouses in Chicago, New York City, LA, Encinitas, Phoenix and Denver. My favorite is Erie. Everyone is pleasant from the valet to the waitstaff. In the summertime they have maybe the best outside dining area in the city. The steaks and seafood are the reasons to frequent Erie though. They provide the best beef, veal and seafood in the city. It is cooked to order and to perfection. The chef will make your order any way you wish from Vesuvio, Oreganato, Italian to Velasco or just plain. The appetizers are terrific. The fried blue cheese ravioli are unique. The full service bar pours a good drink and the wine list is extensive. There is also a room for private parties with its own bar and dining room. Great old fashioned Chicago steakhouse.
